'''Hande Kader''' was a politically active Turkish [[trans woman|transgender woman]]. Kader was familiar to millions of Turks as a [[LGBT social movements|figurehead for the LGBT community]] after being photographed at the forefront of the resistance against police forces suppressing the 2015 [[Gay Pride]] event in [[Istanbul]].<ref name=GuardianUK>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/aug/23/murder-transgender-lgbt-hande-kader-turkey|title=The shocking murder of trans activist Hande Kader says much about Turkey today|last=Shafak|first=Elif|date=2016-08-23|website=The Guardian|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-24}}</ref> In August 2016, she was reported missing by her flatmate Davut Dengiler when she failed to return home the following week.<ref name="BBCNews"/> Her body was found raped, mutilated, and burnt<ref name=DailyMirrorUK>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/transgender-womans-mutilated-body-found-8638180|title=Transgender woman's mutilated body found BURNT in street follows streak of gay hate crimes in Turkey|last=Jones|first=Stephen|date=2016-08-20|website=Daily Mirror|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-22}}</ref> by the roadside in the [[Zekeriyaköy, Istanbul|Zekeriyaköy]] up-market on August 12, 2016.<ref name=dailydot>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailydot.com/irl/istanbul-trans-activist-hande-kader-hate-crime/|title=International outcry following brutal rape, murder of Istanbul trans activist|last=Siese|first=April|date=2016-08-20|website=The Daily Dot|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-21}}</ref> Despite being badly mutilated, Kader's body was identified by prosthetics at the city morgue by Dengiler.<ref name=BBCNews>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-37143879|title=Hande Kader: Outcry in Turkey over transgender woman's murder|last=Arslan|first=Rengin|date=2016-08-21|website=BBC News|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-22}}</ref><ref name="DailyMirrorUK"/>
Kader was employed in the [[sex industry]] as a sex worker, and was last seen getting into a client's car.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mic.com/articles/152097/trans-rights-activist-hande-kader-was-raped-and-burned-to-death-in-turkey|title=Trans rights activist Hande Kader was raped and burned to death in Turkey|last=Harvard|first=Sarah|date=2016-08-19|website=Mic|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-37143879|title=Hande Kader: Outcry in Turkey over transgender woman's murder|last=|first=|date=2016-08-21|website=BBC News|publisher=|language=en-GB|access-date=2016-08-21}}</ref> She was 23 years old at the time of her death.<ref name="l-express"/> The official cause of death has not yet been released. Reports indicate that after death her corpse was set on fire, possibly to avoid identification of the perpetrator(s).<ref name=AlJazeera>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/08/hundreds-protest-murder-trans-woman-istanbul-160821192103933.html|title=Hundreds protest over murder of trans woman in Istanbul|last=|first=|date=2016-08-23|website=Al Jazerra|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-24}}</ref>
Following her death, there has been a public outcry and protests against the mistreatment of transgender people in Turkish society.<ref name=dailydot/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://metro.co.uk/2016/08/20/anger-after-trans-woman-is-raped-and-burned-to-death-in-turkey-6079755/|title=Anger after trans woman is raped and burned to death in Turkey|last=Burke|first=Dave|date=2016-08-20|website=Metro|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2016/08/20/news/turchia_trovata_morta_icona_lgbt_simbolo_lotta_per_gay_pride-146303996/?refresh_ce|title=Turchia, l'orribile morte di Hande Kader, icona Lgbt del Gay Pride vietato a Istanbul|last=|first=|date=2016-08-20|website=Repubblica|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-21}}</ref><ref name="l-express">{{Cite web|url=http://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/monde/europe/assassinat-d-hande-kader-icone-lgbt-manifestation-pour-la-justice-a-istanbul_1823137.html|title=Assassinat d'Hande Kader, icône LGBT: manifestation "pour la justice" à Istanbul|last=|first=|date=2016-08-21|website=L'Express|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-21}}</ref>
